Ingredients

Lime (optional)
Tamarind Paste (optional)
Fish Sauce
Thai Sugar
Soy Sauce
Rice Vinegar

Chicken
Shallot
Garlic
Scallion (optional)
Red Chili (optional)
Egg (optional)
Roasted Peanuts (optional)
Bean Sprouts (optional)

Flat Rice Noodles
Salt
Black Pepper
Paprika (optional)

Instructions

Mix together pad thai sauce: lime, tamarind paste, fish sauce, thai sugar, soy sauce, rice vinegar.
Smash roasted peanuts.
Season chicken with salt, black pepper, paprika. Sauté chicken. Set aside.
Boil water. Take out of heat. Place flat rice noodles in the water.
Sauté thinly sliced shallots, garlic, scallions, red chili in this order. Add egg. Stir together.
Add chicken, rinsed noodles, pad thai sauce, bean sprouts, smashed roasted peanuts. Mix well and stir-fry for a minute.
Add lime juice.

Notes

For more heat, add any hot sauce to pad thai sauce.
